een trained on IYCF',0,1,'Zambia','na'),(111,'q_50','How is the government promoting BFHI principles through advocacy and communication campaigns?','Observation of World Breastfeeding Week',0,1,'Zambia','na'),(112,'q_51','Are there efforts to raise awareness about the importance of breastfeeding at the national level?','Yes, a plan for raising awareness is required to be put in place so it is done systematically.',0,1,'Zambia','na'),(113,'q_52','Is there ongoing research to evaluate the impact of BFHI on maternal and infant health outcomes?','No',0,1,'Zambia','na'),(114,'q_53','Specify if yes:',NULL,0,1,'Zambia','na'),(115,'q_54','Are there initiatives to incorporate innovative approaches to improve BFHI implementation?','Yes',0,1,'Zambia','na'),(116,'q_55','Specify if yes: 2','Utilization of orientation models, targeting BFHI for Level 1, 2 and 3 Hospitals only while the rest of the Health centers focus on IYCF',0,1,'Zambia','na'),(117,'q_56','What are the main challenges faced in the BFHI implementation at the strategic level?','Funding, inadequate understanding on BFHI and IYCF, targeting facilities, when to do BFHI and when to do IYCF',0,1,'Zambia','na'),(118,'q_57','What are the main challenges faced in the BFHI implementation at other levels?','In adequate Coordination, national to provincial level; staff at national level not dedicated to BFHI; No coordinator appointed to BFHI; No implementation guidelines; No working together in RHMCH in BFHI;',0,1,'Zambia','na'),(119,'q_58','What are the identified barriers to the successful integration of BFHI into national health care systems, including MNCH QoC?','Tools for BFHI QoC developed but not yet utilized in QC; System of QC not compatible with BFHI requiremets',0,1,'Zambia','na'),(120,'q_59','How is the government addressing these challenges?','Not yet done; not presented to QC',0,1,'Zambia','na'),(121,'q_60','What do you think we can do at regional and national levels to improve the implementation of the Baby Friendly Hospital Initiative?','Advocacy at PS level to focus on Budget allocation, staff allocation; integration of service management at Department level',0,1,'Zambia','na'),(122,'q_61','What support do you need from WHO and partners to strengthen and scale up the implementation of the BFHI in your country?','Dedicated staff at national level; Fund allocation; identification of priority health facilities for BFHI.  Need clarification on when to use BFHI and when to use IYCF.  Advocacy for resource allocation to WHO; Focus on pre-service training',0,1,'Zambia','na'),(123,'q_1','Name of the country','Uganda',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(124,'q_2','Was a consultative process used in the collection of information in this questionnaire?','Yes',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(125,'q_3','If yes, please specify what consultative mechanism was used','Hybrid (both physical and virtual',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(126,'q_4','Has the country\'s breastfeeding/infant feeding policies and guidelines incorporated- all the 10 steps to successful breastfeeding been developed and disseminated?','Yes',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(127,'q_5','Do the policies protect breastfeeding by prohibiting all promotion of breastmilk substitutes, feeding bottles, and teats?','Yes',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(128,'q_6','Do the policies prohibit the distribution of gift packs with commercial samples and supplies or promotional materials for these products to pregnant women and mothers?','Yes',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(129,'q_7','Are the following national regulations being updated to align with BFHI guidelines? (Multiple choice answer)','a. Code of Marketing of Breast Milk Substitutes ;b. paid maternity leave;c. Breastfeeding facilities at the workplace ;',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(130,'q_8','Are the policies, including conflicts of interest and health workers\' responsibilities, around the Code?','Yes',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(131,'q_9','Is there a dedicated national budget allocated for the BFHI implementation or to support breastfeeding?','No',0,1,'Uganda','n