hrough well established coordination structures starting with the MIYCAN/BFHI thematic working group that feeds into the Nutrition Technical working group, that reports to the Health Sector Senior Management Committee, then Senior Top management committee. Additionally, the MIYCAN/BFHI Thematic working group networks with other relevant departments such MCH, Quality Assurance and Standards etc.',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(140,'q_18','Are there collaborations with non-governmental organizations (NGOs), international agencies, and other stakeholders to support BFHI?','Yes',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(141,'q_19','How do WHO, UNICEF and USAID coordinate support to the country in strengthening the implementation of the BFHI? (To be responded to by the WHO, UNICEF and USAID staff) _x000D_\n','Coordination of support to the country for nutrition (in general) is done by the Nutrition Development Partners Group. However, there has not been special focus/agenda for BFHI',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(142,'q_20','Does the country have  a specific acceleration plan in place for the BFHI implementation? ','Yes, the country is  implementing the MIYCAN action plan (2021-2025, three quarters of which is BFHI related); and the Reproductive Maternal Newborn, Child & Adolescent Healthy Aging sharpened Plan II (2023-2027).',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(143,'q_21','How many health facilities are there in your country ?','7,889',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(144,'q_22','How many health facilities in your country offer maternity services?','2,031',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(145,'q_23','How many health facilities in your country offering maternity services are implementing the ten steps for successful breastfeeding?','132 (officially accredited), however, there are more  facilities implementing the ten steps but have not be assessed officially to be accredited baby friendly',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(146,'q_24','Have all health facilities with maternity services been assessed for BFHI compliance?','No',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(147,'q_25','Is there a recognized mechanism for community-based support to mothers for BFHI (Step 10)?','Yes; we\'re using the Village Health Team structure and more recently under MIYCAN rolling out the care groups/mother support groups at community level. However, the coverage is still limited.',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(148,'q_26','Is breastfeeding education incorporated into the training of health professionals?','Yes',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(149,'q_27','If yes, provide details.','Maternal and Child Health is a key component/module in the training packages of health professionals and this entails specific sessions on breastfeeding promotion, protection and support. Routinely in the health facilities, breastfeeding education topics are well integrated in the CMEs/CPDs',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(150,'q_28','Are the Ten Steps covered in pre-service training of health professionals?','Yes',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(151,'q_29','If yes provide details.','Different cadres such Medical officers, midwives, nutritionist, and Tutors by national standards have to take courses on Infant and Young Child feeding, maternal nutrition and the like before they are passed out.',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(152,'q_30','What continuing education courses are provided on the Ten Steps?','IYCF (breastfeeding counseling and support), ANC preparation, Care for women, newborns and children including the sick newborns, Policies supportive of breastfeeding promotion and protection, Management of breastfeeding complications,',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(153,'q_31','What is being done to incorporate the Ten Steps more fully into pre-service training?','Revision of the guidelines and training packages, revision of teaching Institutions curricular',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(154,'q_32','Are there joint training programs that combine the Ten Steps to Successful Breastfeeding with other relevant health competencies, such as maternal health or newborn or PNC training packages, and I...','Yes',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(155,'q_33','Does the country have a national pool of trainers on the BFHI that has been active in the last two years?','Yes',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(156,'q_34','How many healthcare providers have been trained on BFHI in the last two years?','None (last trained in 2019)',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(157,'q_35','Is there a system in place to ensure continuous training on breastfeeding support? ','No',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(158,'q_36','Does the training cover all Ten Steps to Successful Breastfeeding and the International Code of Marketing of Breast-milk Substitutes?','Yes',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(159,'q_37','Are the BFHI quality statements and measures incorporated in national MNCH QoC strategies and documents?','Yes',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(160,'q_38','Are the national or sub-national BFHI or BF focal persons represented in MNCH QoC Network working groups?','No',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(161,'q_39','Are the BFHI quality statements and measures included in national or sub-national QoC supporting materials, including QI/supportive supervision, capacity-building, and facility QI tools (HMIS, sco...','Yes',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(162,'q_40','Do facilities QI teams conduct regular measurements and review of BFHI or BF quality indicators','Yes',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(163,'q_41','Are there any aspects of the Ten Steps assessed in health facility accreditation processes, including in the private sector?','No',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(164,'q_42','Is there a system in place to systematically assess the implementation of BFHI in functional health facilities?','Yes',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(165,'q_43','Have any changes been made during the last two years to streamline the BFHI assessment process?','No',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(166,'q_44','Does your routine HMIS/DHIS2 collect information on the percentage of infants being breastfed within one hour after birth?','Yes',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(167,'q_45','Which other indicators related to breastfeeding are analyzed in routine in your National HMIS/DHIS2?','Proportion of postnatal mothers who received  IYCF counseling_x000D_\nProportion of postnatal mothers who received  maternal nutrition counseling _x000D_\nNumbers of mothers who practiced skin-to-skin care_x000D_\nNumber of HIV exposed infants exclusively breastfeeding _x000D_\nNumber of HIV exposed  infants breastfeeding up to one year _x000D_\n _x000D_\n',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(168,'q_46','What indicators are used to measure the success of BFHI at the national level?','Rate of initiation of breastfeeding within one hour after birth_x000D_\nRate of exclusively breastfeeding for the first 6 months of age_x000D_\nProportion of children continuing to breastfeed up to 2 years and beyond_x000D_\nNumber of health facilities accredited baby friendly_x000D_\nNumber of breastfeeding facilities/corners established in work places (both formal and informal)_x000D_\n',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(169,'q_47','Are there community-based initiatives to complement hospital efforts?','Yes',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(170,'q_48','If yes specify ','VHT structure and the mother care groups',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(171,'q_49','How is the community involved in promoting and supporting breastfeeding practices?','Follow of mothers discharged from HFs, provide breastfeeding counseling and support, help in identification and referral of mother and children in need of special care',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(172,'q_50','How is the government promoting BFHI principles through advocacy and communication campaigns?','Through commemoration of World Breastfeeding Week, _x000D_\nDevelopment of IEC materials and mass dissemination of these materials at all levels,_x000D_\nMedia engagements; radio and Tv talk shows or programs, poems, Music dance and drama, articles in news papers, organizing webinars, use of social media platforms,_x000D_\nStake holder consultative advocacy meetings with policy and decision makers at different levels_x000D_\n',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(173,'q_51','Are there efforts to raise awareness about the importance of breastfeeding at the national level?','Yes',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(174,'q_52','Is there ongoing research to evaluate the impact of BFHI on maternal and infant health outcomes?','No',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(175,'q_53','Specify if yes:',NULL,0,1,'Uganda','na'),(176,'q_54','Are there initiatives to incorporate innovative approaches to improve BFHI implementation?','No',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(177,'q_55','Specify if yes: 2',NULL,0,1,'Uganda','na'),(178,'q_56','What are the main challenges faced in the BFHI implementation at the strategic level?','The biggest challenge is inadequate funding for BFHI-no budget_x000D_\nWeak integration in service delivery and parallel implementation by some implementing partners_x000D_\nData gaps; information system largely paper based and not very efficient in producing quality data',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(179,'q_57','What are the main challenges faced in the BFHI implementation at other levels?','Inadequate resource envelop_x000D_\nInadequate knowledge, skills and competencies in BFHI_x000D_\nPoor infrastructure_x000D_\nAggressive marketing of breastmilk substitutes_x000D_\n _x000D_\n',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(180,'q_58','What are the identified barriers to the successful integration of BFHI into national health care systems, including MNCH QoC?','Inability to build capacity of health care providers on BFHI due to limited funds_x000D_\nLow staffing levels at health facilities_x000D_\nPoor infrastructure e.g limited bed capacity _x000D_\nPoor health worker attitudes_x000D_\nLack of knowledge among health facility managers/leaders to champion BFHI issues_x000D_\n',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(181,'q_59','How is the government addressing these challenges?','Policy review and formulation e.g health workforce structure has been revised for regional Referral and General Hospitals and lower health centres._x000D_\nIncreasing awareness and advocacy for BFHI prioritization (budget allocation)_x000D_\nPromoting CPDs and CMEs as part of key performance indicator at HF level_x000D_\nStrengthening QI integration in health facility service delivery,',0,1,'Uganda','na'),(182,'q_60','What do you think we can do at regional and national levels to improve the implementation of the Baby Friendly Hospital Initiative?','Ring-fence a budget for BFHI implementation_x000D_\nBuild capacity of frontline health care providers on BFHI, refresher training at regular intervals_x000D_\nRe-enforce Code monitoring_x000D_\nIntegration of BFHI in pre-service training of relevant health cadres_x000D_\nRoutine monitoring and assessment of BFHI implementation_x000D_\nStrengthen partner coordination_x000D_\n',0,1,'Uganda','na');
